definition.value: an injury AE that has the finding of damage to the ear during a surgical procedure.
an injury AE that has the finding of damage to the kidney during a surgical procedure.
an injury AE finding of damage to the skin during a surgical procedure.
an injury AE that has the finding of damage to the spleen during a surgical procedure.
an injury AE that has the finding of damage to a vein during a surgical procedure.
an injury AE that has the finding of damage to the jugular vein.

an appendicitis AE that has acute inflammation to the vermiform appendix caused by a pathogenic agent with gangrenous changes resulting in the rupture of the appendiceal wall. The appendiceal wall rupture causes the release of inflammatory and bacterial contents from the appendiceal lumen into the abdominal cavity.
a troponin AE which indicates increased levels of cardiac troponin T in a biological specimen
an eye infection AE that has an infectious process involving the conjunctiva. Clinical manifestations include pink or red color in the eyes.
an eye infection AE that has an infectious process involving the internal structures of the eye.
an eye infection AE that has an infectious process involving the orbit of the eye.
an eye infection AE that has an infectious process involving the cornea.
a fatigue AE that has fatigue relieved by rest
a fatigue AE that has fatigue not relieved by rest; limiting instrumental activities of daily living
a fatigue AE that has fatigue not relieved by rest, limiting self care activities of daily living
a myocardial infarction AE that has asymptomatic and cardiac enzymes minimally abnormal and no evidence of ischemic ECG changes
a myocardial infarction AE that has severe symptoms; cardiac enzymes abnormal; hemodynamically stable; ECG changes consistent with infarction
a pancreatitis AE that has enzyme elevation or radiologic findings only
a pancreatitis AE that has severe pain; vomiting; medical intervention indicated (e.g., analgesia, nutritional support)

label.value: Grade 1 activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE

definition.value: an activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE that is greater than the upper limit of normal to 1.5 times the upper limit of normal

label.value: Grade 2 activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE

definition.value: an activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE that is 1.5-2.5 times the upper limit of normal

label.value: Grade 3 activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE

definition.value: an activated partial thromboplastin time prolonged AE that is greater than 2.5 times the upper limit of normal; hemorrhage

label.value: Grade 1 alanine aminotransferase level increased AE

definition.value: an alanine aminotransferase level increased AE that is greater than the upper limit of normal to 3 times the upper limit of normal

label.value: Grade 2 alanine aminotransferase level increased AE

definition.value: an alanine aminotransferase level increased AE that is greater than 3 to 5 times the upper limit of normal

label.value: Grade 3 alanine aminotransferase level increased AE

definition.value: an alanine aminotransferase level increased AE that is greater than 5 to 20 times the upper limit of normal

label.value: Grade 4 alanine aminotransferase level increased AE

definition.value: an alanine aminotransferase level increased AE that is greater than 20 times the upper limit of normal
an anal ulcer AE that is symptomatic; altered GI function
an anal ulcer AE that has severely altered GI function; TPN indicated; elective operative or endoscopic intervention indicated; disabling
an atrial flutter AE that has symptomatic and incompletely controlled medically, or controlled with device (e.g., pacemaker), or ablation
an otitis media AE that is localized; local intervention indicated (e.g., topical antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral)
an otitis media AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic or operative intervention indicated
a pericarditis AE that has asymptomatic, ECG or physical findings (e.g., rub) consistent with pericarditis
a pericarditis AE that has symptomatic pericarditis (e.g., chest pain)
a pericarditis AE that has pericarditis with physiologic consequences (e.g., pericardial constriction)
a pharyngitis AE that is localized; local intervention indicated (e.g., topical antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral)
a pharyngitis AE where IV antibiotic, antifungal, or antiviral intervention indicated; radiologic or operative intervention indicated
a fever AE that has 38.0 - 39.0 degrees C (100.4 - 102.2 degrees F)
a fever AE that has greater than 39.0 - 40.0 degrees C (102.3 - 104.0 degrees F)
a fever AE that has greater than 40.0 degrees C (greater than104.0 degrees F) for less than or equal to 24 hrs
a fever AE that has greater than 40.0 degrees C (greater than104.0 degrees F) for more than 24 hrs
an injection-site adverse event characterized by tenderness with or without associated symptoms (e.g., warmth, erythema, itching)
an injection-site adverse event characterized by pain; lipodystrophy; edema; phlebitis
an injection-site adverse event characterized by ulceration or necrosis; severe tissue damage; operative intervention indicated
a leukocyte cell number increased AE where leukocytes are greater than 100,000/mm3
a leukocyte cell number increased AE that has clinical manifestations of leucostasis; urgent intervention indicated

label.value: Grade 1 leukocyte cell number decreased AE

definition.value: a leukocyte cell number decreased AE that is less than the lower limit of normal - 3000/mm3; less than the lower limit of normal - 3.0 x 10e9 /L

label.value: Grade 2 leukocyte cell number decreased AE

definition.value: a leukocyte cell number decreased AE that is less than 3000 - 2000/mm3; less than 3.0 - 2.0 x 10e9 /L

label.value: Grade 3 leukocyte cell number decreased AE

definition.value: a leukocyte cell number decreased AE that is less than 2000 - 1000/mm3; less than 2.0 - 1.0 x 10e9 /L

label.value: Grade 4 leukocyte cell number decreased AE

definition.value: a leukocyte cell number decreased AE that is less than 1000/mm3; less than 1.0 x 10e9 /L
a malaise AE that has uneasiness or lack of well being
